answerBox.snippet: How much is the 1945 No Mint mark Wheat Penny worth? Most 1945 Wheat cents produced in Philadelphia are affordable, and most are worth $0.25 to 55. However, highly-graded red specimens often reach $180 to $220, except for rare and valuable MS 68-ranking pieces. Their estimated price range is roughly $5,000 to $6,000.
